Olalekan Adetayo, Abuja The National Working Committee of the African Democratic Congress has dissolved the party’s executive committee in Ogun State. It set up a caretaker/transition committee to handle the affairs of the party in the state. The dissolution, which was with immediate effect, was contained in a statement jointly signed by the party’s National Chairman, Chief Ralphs Nwosu; and the National Secretary, Alhaji Said Baba Abdullahi, on Thursday. The statement read, “Pursuant to Article 13, Section 14 (IV) of the Constitution of the African Democratic Congress, the National Working Committee hereby dissolves the Ogun State Executive Committee. This dissolution takes immediate effect. “The NWC has also approved the appointment of a caretaker/transition committee. “The members are: Ambassador Olugbenga Shobowale – Chairman; Odunlami Salami – Secretary; and Yemisi Omotayo, Bolanle Oduwaiye, Yetunde Osho, Adebambo Olajonlu and Abiola Odutola as members.” Copyright PUNCH.
